hh3cVoCallActive.name: hh3cVoCallActive

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hh3cVoCallActive.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cVoCallActive.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of voice call active record information.

Hh3cGUid.name: Hh3cGUid
Hh3cGUid.description: Represents a global call identifier. The global call identifier is used as an unique identifier for an end-to-end call. A zero length Hh3cGUid indicates no value for the global call identifier.

hh3cVoiceCallActiveTable.name: hh3cVoiceCallActiveTable
hh3cVoiceCallActiveTable.description: This table is the voice extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice encapsulation call leg information that is derived from the statistics of lower layer telephony interface.

hh3cVoiceCallActiveEntry.name: hh3cVoiceCallActiveEntry
hh3cVoiceCallActiveEntry.description: The information regarding a single voice encapsulation call leg. The call leg entry is identified by using the same index objects that are used by call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB to identify the call. An entry of this table is created when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created and call active entry contains the call establishment to a voice over telephony network peer. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

hh3cVoCallActiveConnectionId.name: hh3cVoCallActiveConnectionId
hh3cVoCallActiveConnectionId.description: The global call identifier for the gateway call.

hh3cVoCallActiveTxDuration.name: hh3cVoCallActiveTxDuration
hh3cVoCallActiveTxDuration.description: Duration of transmit path open from this peer to the voice gateway for the call. The units is milliseconds.

hh3cVoCallActiveVoiceTxDuration.name: hh3cVoCallActiveVoiceTxDuration
hh3cVoCallActiveVoiceTxDuration.description: Duration of voice transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The voice utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by hh3cVoCallActiveTXDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

hh3cVoCallActiveFaxTxDuration.name: hh3cVoCallActiveFaxTxDuration
hh3cVoCallActiveFaxTxDuration.description: Duration of fax transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The fax utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by hh3cVoCallActiveTXDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

hh3cVoCallActiveCoderType.name: hh3cVoCallActiveCoderType
hh3cVoCallActiveCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the PSTN leg of a call.

hh3cVoCallActiveImgPageCount.name: hh3cVoCallActiveImgPageCount
hh3cVoCallActiveImgPageCount.description: The number of fax related image pages are received or transmitted via the peer for the call. The units is pages.

hh3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveTable.name: hh3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveTable
hh3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveTable.description: This table is the VoIP extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains VoIP call leg information about specific VoIP call destination.

hh3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveEntry.name: hh3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveEntry
hh3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveEntry.description: The information regarding a single VoIP call leg. The call leg entry is identified by using the same index objects that are used by call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB to identify the call. An entry of this table is created when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created and the call active entry contains information for the call establishment to the peer on the IP backbone via a voice over IP peer. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveConnectionId.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveConnectionId
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveConnectionId.description: The global call identifier for the gateway call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPType.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPType
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPType.description: The type of remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPAddr.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPAddr
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPAddr.description: Remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigPort.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigPort
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigPort.description: Remote system UDP listener signalling port to which to transmit voice packets.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPType.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPType
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPType.description: The type of remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPAddr.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPAddr
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPAddr.description: Remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedPort.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedPort
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedPort.description: Remote system UDP listener media port to which to transmit voice packets.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveSessProtocol.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveSessProtocol
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveSessProtocol.description: The object specifies the session protocol to be used for internet call between local and remote router via IP backbone.

hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveCoderType.name: hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveCoderType
hh3cVoVoIPCallActiveCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the VoIP leg of a call.
